<subSubSection id="B699651BFFAD3F3CFF74F848009BD6F6" pageId="11" pageNumber="108" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="FE3C3690FFAD3F3CFF74F848009BD6F6" blockId="11.[151,1437,1660,2009]" pageId="11" pageNumber="108">
<emphasis id="CCF7EA82FFAD3F3CFF74F8480063D69A" bold="true" box="[199,334,1948,1973]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="108" reason="1">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species epithet, 
<taxonomicName id="39834D13FFAD3F3CFDE7F8480238D69A" box="[596,789,1948,1973]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Afrostoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadripunctatum">
<emphasis id="CCF7EA82FFAD3F3CFDE7F8480238D69A" box="[596,789,1948,1973]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="108">quadripunctatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, is an adjective referring to the four yellow punctate maculae on the abdomen.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="AAFC6618FFAA3F3BFF24F8C6036AD668" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4928799" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4928799" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4928799/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="109" startId="12.[151,248,1810,1832]" targetBox="[151,1423,204,1782]" targetPageId="12">
<paragraph id="FE3C3690FFAA3F3BFF24F8C6036AD668" blockId="12.[151,1436,1810,1863]" pageId="12" pageNumber="109">
<emphasis id="CCF7EA82FFAA3F3BFF24F8C6003CD607" bold="true" box="[151,273,1810,1832]" pageId="12" pageNumber="109">FIGURE 2.</emphasis>
50% majority rule consensus cladogram of 
<taxonomicName id="39834D13FFAA3F3BFD61F8C60201D607" baseAuthorityName="Rotheray and Gilbert" baseAuthorityYear="1999" box="[722,812,1810,1832]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Bacchini">
<emphasis id="CCF7EA82FFAA3F3BFD61F8C60201D607" box="[722,812,1810,1832]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="109">Bacchini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species produced from Bayesian analysis of COI data. Clade supports shown are posterior probabilities.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption id="AAFC6618FFAB3F3AFF24FBE70571D58A" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4928801" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4928801" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4928801/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="110" startId="13.[151,250,1075,1097]" targetBox="[158,1426,179,1048]" targetPageId="13">
<paragraph id="FE3C3690FFAB3F3AFF24FBE70571D58A" blockId="13.[151,1436,1075,1189]" pageId="13" pageNumber="110">
<emphasis id="CCF7EA82FFAB3F3AFF24FBE7003ED566" bold="true" box="[151,275,1075,1097]" pageId="13" pageNumber="110">FIGURE 3.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="39834D13FFAB3F3AFEA9FBE70269D566" authority="Skevington &amp; Thompson" authorityName="Skevington &amp; Thompson" box="[282,836,1075,1097]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Afrostoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadripunctatum">
<emphasis id="CCF7EA82FFAB3F3AFEA9FBE70315D566" box="[282,568,1075,1097]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="110">Afrostoma quadripunctatum</emphasis>
Skevington &amp; Thompson
</taxonomicName>
, male genitalia: A. epandrium, lateral view; B. epandrium, dorsal view; C. hypandrium, lateral view; D. aedeagal complex, lateral view. Abbreviations: cerc—cercus; distph—distiphallus; ej apod—ejaculatory apodeme; epand—epandrium; hyp—hypandrium; phalapod—phallapodeme; pgt—postgonite; smp dt—sperm duct; spm sac—sperm sac; sur—surstylus. Scale bar: 0.1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection id="B699651BFFAB3F3AFF74FB060318D455" pageId="13" pageNumber="110" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="FE3C3690FFAB3F3AFF74FB060318D455" blockId="13.[151,1436,1234,1403]" pageId="13" pageNumber="110">
<emphasis id="CCF7EA82FFAB3F3AFF74FB060061D5C4" bold="true" box="[199,332,1234,1259]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="110" reason="1">Discussion.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="39834D13FFAB3F3AFEE6FB0603B9D5C4" box="[341,660,1234,1259]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Afrostoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadripunctatum">
<emphasis id="CCF7EA82FFAB3F3AFEE6FB0603B9D5C4" box="[341,660,1234,1259]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="110">Afrostoma quadripunctatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is superficially similar to 
<taxonomicName id="39834D13FFAB3F3AFC75FB060413D5C4" authority="Becker" authorityName="Becker. Skevington" authorityYear="1909" box="[966,1342,1234,1259]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Melanostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="infuscatum">
<emphasis id="CCF7EA82FFAB3F3AFC75FB0605C9D5C4" box="[966,1252,1234,1259]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="110">Melanostoma infuscatum</emphasis>
Becker
</taxonomicName>
, but the yellow abdominal maculae are much smaller and the facial tubercle is more abrupt and prominent than those in 
<taxonomicName id="39834D13FFAB3F3AFF24FACE003FD41C" authorityName="Becker. Skevington" authorityYear="1909" box="[151,274,1306,1331]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Melanostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="infuscatum">
<emphasis id="CCF7EA82FFAB3F3AFF24FACE003FD41C" box="[151,274,1306,1331]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="110">infuscatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The type series of 
<taxonomicName id="39834D13FFAB3F3AFE4FFACE03FDD41C" authority="Becker" authorityName="Becker. Skevington" authorityYear="1909" box="[508,720,1306,1331]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Melanostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="infuscatum">
<emphasis id="CCF7EA82FFAB3F3AFE4FFACE035AD41C" box="[508,631,1306,1331]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="110">infuscatum</emphasis>
Becker
</taxonomicName>
(
<specimenCount id="E885FD19FFAB3F3AFD50FACE026DD41C" box="[739,832,1306,1331]" pageId="13" pageNumber="110" type="male">2 males</specimenCount>
, 
<specimenCount id="E885FD19FFAB3F3AFCFDFACE0290D41C" box="[846,957,1306,1331]" pageId="13" pageNumber="110" type="female">2 females</specimenCount>
in Paris) was examined and herewith we validate the unpublished 
<typeStatus id="21388832FFAB3F3AFE71FAEA0304D478" box="[450,553,1342,1367]" pageId="13" pageNumber="110">lectotype</typeStatus>
selected by Kassebeer (a male, labeled by him) to ensure consistent and universal interpretation of this name.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
